# ARD OKO manifests

Generated by `ansible/roles/deploy_oko`.

## Bootstrap

`bootstrap/` contains resources that are safe to apply before OKO CRDs exist:

```bash
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_bootstrap_workdir }}
```

## Operators

`operators/` installs the OpenStack operator through OLM using:

- catalog source: `{{ oko_operator_catalog_source }}`
- catalog image: `{{ oko_operator_catalog_image }}`
- subscription channel: `{{ oko_openstack_subscription_channel }}`

```bash
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_operators_workdir }}
```

## Network

`network/` contains first-pass OKO network inputs:

- `NetConfig` for `ctlplane`, `internalapi`, `storage`, and `tenant`
- NetworkAttachmentDefinitions using macvlan/whereabouts defaults from install_yamls-style examples

Apply after the OpenStack operator CRDs exist and before the control plane/dataplane:

```bash
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_network_workdir }}
```

Role setting: `oko_apply_network_resources={{ oko_apply_network_resources }}`.

## Control plane

`controlplane/` contains a compact OpenStackControlPlane base using:

- Kubernetes storage class: `{{ oko_k8s_storage_class }}`
- Cinder backend: `{{ oko_cinder_backend }}`
- Cinder NFS share: `{{ oko_cinder_nfs_share | default(oko_nfs_server ~ ':' ~ oko_nfs_export_path) }}`

Apply after the OpenStack operator CRDs exist:

```bash
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_controlplane_workdir }}
```

Full staged order:

```bash
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_operators_workdir }}
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_network_workdir }}
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_controlplane_workdir }}
{{ oko_kube_client | default('oc') }} --kubeconfig {{ oko_kubeconfig }} apply -k {{ oko_dataplane_workdir }}
```

Role setting: `oko_apply_controlplane_resources={{ oko_apply_controlplane_resources }}`.

## Dataplane

`dataplane/` creates EDPM NodeSet/Deployment input for: {{ oko_edpm_nodes | map(attribute='name') | list | join(', ') }}

Dataplane apply remains guarded because the current first-pass input assumes a `ctlplane` network/subnet and no full network-isolation base has been rendered yet.

Role setting: `oko_apply_dataplane_resources={{ oko_apply_dataplane_resources }}`.

## Legacy generated inputs

`generated/` preserves the first-pass generated patch/dataplane files for inspection and comparison while the role moves to explicit `operators/`, `controlplane/`, and `dataplane/` phases.
